&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Neonatal Clinical Support Worker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting a motivated, dedicated and caring neonatal clinical support worker with previous hospital experience to join our friendly team on the Special Care Baby Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Neonatal Clinical Support Worker will primarily work alongside the Neonatal Nursing Team, Neonatal Nurse Practitioner, Midwives and mothers in caring for neonates requiring support in a Special Care or Transitional Care setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our SCBU has 12 cots and we strive to deliver family-centred care, helping to support loving relationships with parents and their babies on this journey. This role will complement the care that the nursing and medical staff provide to the family.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further queries, please get in touch with Senior Sister Giezl Pulanco on extension 6564 and/or Fiona England on extension 4701&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
